1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,994
[The Age of Awakening]

2
00:00:01,994 --> 00:00:04,950
[Episode Fourteen]

3
00:00:05,360 --> 00:00:06,640
My apologies, everybody,

4
00:00:06,960 --> 00:00:07,840
I have a guest from my hometown here.

5
00:00:08,240 --> 00:00:09,120
How about we continue next time?

6
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:12,240
We haven't fully enjoyed our discussion yet, how come it's over now?

7
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:13,120
I'm terribly sorry!

8
00:00:12,523 --> 00:00:14,203
[Hu Shi, styled Shizhi, Professor at Peking University]

9
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:14,160
Professor Hu,

10
00:00:14,320 --> 00:00:16,720
can we say goodbye to you in the Western manner?

11
00:00:16,880 --> 00:00:17,680
Of course!

12
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:25,440
See you next time, Doctor Hu.

13
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:26,160
Thanks for coming here.

14
00:00:27,840 --> 00:00:28,240
Come on.

15
00:00:30,364 --> 00:00:32,404
[Wang Mengzou, Manager of Yadong Library]

16
00:00:31,680 --> 00:00:32,480
Thanks.

17
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:33,760
Goodbye, Doctor Hu.

18
00:00:36,560 --> 00:00:37,600
Thank you.

19
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:42,560
See you, Doctor Hu.

20
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:45,920
Come here.

21
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:47,920
See you next time.

22
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:51,360
Goodbye, Doctor Hu.

23
00:00:54,720 --> 00:00:55,520
Brother Mengzou,

24
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:56,560
Doctor Hu.

25
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:57,920
Don't forget to eat more apples!

26
00:00:58,240 --> 00:00:59,120
For the vitamin.

27
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:00,400
Sure, thank you!

28
00:01:04,160 --> 00:01:04,880
See you, Doctor Hu.

29
00:01:05,280 --> 00:01:06,000
See you.

30
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:08,240
Take care.

31
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:16,320
Brother Mengzou, it's been a while.

32
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:22,240
Good to see you!

33
00:01:23,520 --> 00:01:24,960
Come over here to sit.

34
00:01:29,440 --> 00:01:30,000
Here...

35
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:30,720
I'll take it.

36
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:40,720
Brother Mengzou,

37
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:43,600
You must be just arriving.

38
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:45,920
So here is the thing,

39
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:47,520
now that "New Youth" had

40
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:48,400
adopted collective editorship,

41
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:50,480
I'm here to establish the distribution station.

42
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:53,920
I wasn't able to find Zhongfu, so I decided to come to you.

43
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:56,080
Brother Zhongfu went to the Shaoxing Guildhall today.

44
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:05,040
I thought there aren't any female

45
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,160
faculties or students at Peking University.

46
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:07,120
That's true.

47
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:07,840
But,

48
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:08,400
just now...

49
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:11,360
You're talking about the ladies in my office earlier?

50
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,360
They're members of my poetry club in Beijing.

51
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,520
And they're here to discuss vernacular poetry with me.

52
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:21,600
No wonder your mother was so worried about you.

53
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:25,920
Excuse me?

54
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:28,960
Your mother had a letter sent to me

55
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:31,120
saying that back in your hometown,

56
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,440
there were loads of gossips,

57
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:34,880
and rumors about you.

58
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:37,680
Dongxiu was rather anxious at home.

59
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:39,600
So was your mother.

60
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:43,600
Therefore, they asked me to persuade you

61
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,200
to go back home and marry Dongxiu as soon as possible.

62
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:46,640
You see,

63
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:49,280
here's the letter.

64
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:51,200
You should think it over.

65
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:53,680
What you said got me really confused here.

66
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:11,440
You see?

67
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:12,960
What the heck are these?

68
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:15,280
Sheer nonsense! Brother Mengzou.

69
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,400
I too thought they were completely unfounded, before I arrived here.

70
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:19,120
Right!

71
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:21,920
But then, you guys are even talking about "vitamins",

72
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,440
So it's not all rumor after all.

73
00:03:23,680 --> 00:03:26,000
Brother Mengzou, please don't get it wrong.

74
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:28,080
They're indeed the members of my poetry club in Beijing.

75
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:29,920
How can I put it, you're just...

76
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:32,320
But you, you guys were...

77
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,560
That's just common etiquette.

78
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,160
I...

79
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:41,360
This lad Ren Guangming is still quite the drinker!

80
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:45,280
Such a rare opportunity,

81
00:03:45,685 --> 00:03:48,190
[Zhou Shuren (Lu Xun), styled Yucai, Civil servant under the Ministry of Education]

82
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:48,000
for us alumni to gather up in Beijing.

83
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,600
Such a rare gathering.

84
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:52,640
I forgot to ask Guangming just now

85
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:54,000
what's Yang Kaiming up to recently.

86
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:55,680
How come we haven't heard from him in a long time?

87
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:59,120
Ren Guangming said, after Yang Kaiming graduated from the Normal University，

88
00:03:56,555 --> 00:04:00,283
[Zhou Zuoren, styled Xingshao, Professor at Peking University]

89
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,800
he went back home to teach.

90
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,480
He's a kindhearted fellow.

91
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,240
He often gives financial support to a widow,

92
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,840
which reproached by her clansmen.

93
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:07,760
There was one day,

94
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:08,960
Yang Kaiming got drunk,

95
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:11,120
and fell asleep next to the table at the widow's.

96
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,840
The next dawn, somehow her clansmen got informed,

97
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,040
and then

98
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,720
they detained her for denouncement.

99
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:18,560
The head of the clan held a meeting.

100
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:20,000
According to the rules of their clan,

101
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,760
they decided to drown the widow to punish her.

102
00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:25,680
Yang Kaiming was so traumatized hearing what happened that he lost his mind.

103
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:27,040
Nowadays,

104
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:29,440
he begs and gibbers on the street all day long.

105
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,360
He won't recognize anybody anymore.

106
00:04:34,080 --> 00:04:35,120
Madness!

107
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:38,240
People became mad.

108
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:40,880
So did the world.

109
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:45,280
Don't!

110
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:46,560
Don't kill me! Don't kill me!

111
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:47,680
I don't wanna die!

112
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:48,960
I'm begging you!

113
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:50,720
I'm begging you! Please, please don't kill me!

114
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:51,680
I don't wanna die!

115
00:04:52,640 --> 00:04:52,960
I really don't!

116
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:53,360
Hey, Jiusun, what on earth...

117
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:53,840
What do you want?!

118
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:57,120
Cou..cousin...

119
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:59,120
Cousin, you got to save me!

120
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:00,480
Somebody is going to kill me!

121
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:00,800
What?

122
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:02,160
They're chasing after me to kill me!

123
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:02,560
Don't!!

124
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:03,920
No, no, no!!! Don't open the door!

125
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,200
Don't! Don't open the door!!

126
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:06,240
Don't open the door!! Don't!!!

127
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,120
But, Jiusun, what's...

128
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:08,240
They...Listen...

129
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:09,360
Their footsteps!

130
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:10,640
Listen you two!

131
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:13,520
Can't you hear them coming close?

132
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:16,320
They're holding a 10-inch knife,

133
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,800
very sharp - it's bloody!

134
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,080
It's all bloody outside!!

135
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,440
They're going to kill me with that knife!

136
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:23,360
I...I don't want to die!

137
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,400
I have to hide.

138
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:25,920
I have to hide somewhere!

139
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:30,800
No, hide somewhere...

140
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,680
Jiusun, come over here, come on.

141
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:34,880
Wait a bit...

142
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:35,920
No...

143
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:38,880
I don't wanna die...

144
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,000
I don't wanna die at all!!

145
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:42,560
You're just a secretary from Taiyuan

146
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,000
coming to visit in Beijing -- nobody knows you here!

147
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:45,280
Who would kill you?

148
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:46,800
How come someone wants to kill you?

149
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:47,760
Come on,

150
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:48,880
Get out of that first.

151
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:54,480
Cousin, if I die,

152
00:05:56,080 --> 00:06:00,720
can you bring this letter to my mum and sister?

153
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:05,600
He looks deranged, must have lost his mind.

154
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:08,080
Jiusun, you just come out first.

155
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:09,600
We'll talk it over, is that okay?

156
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:10,640
I won't go out!

157
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:12,080
I won't!

158
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:13,040
Please be good and get out first.

159
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,240
I won't go! Don't drag me!

160
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:15,440
Just come out please.

161
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:16,640
Get out!

162
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:18,640
Hurry up, be good, get out now!

163
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:19,840
No, I won't, I won't go!

164
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:20,720
Just come here, will you?

165
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:21,360
I won't!!

166
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:22,880
Come over, be good, come on...

167
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:24,240
They're here!

168
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,080
Just get out first!

169
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:26,880
They're here!

170
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:28,480
I won't go!!!

171
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:31,440
Jiusun, it's me, Jiusun!

172
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:32,960
You guys are here.

173
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:35,440
What on earth happened to him?

174
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,920
On our way to Beijing, Jiusun had

175
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:39,280
seen many people who were starved to death.

176
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,160
He had a breakdown.

177
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:41,280
In these few days when we're staying at the inn,

178
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,200
he kept moving into new rooms.

179
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:44,720
But still he can't sleep at all,

180
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:46,800
as he was horrified that somebody would kill him.

181
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:48,320
This morning,

182
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,600
he insisted on coming to you

183
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,440
and that those people are after him again.

184
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:55,200
It seems that he's having a psychosis.

185
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,680
Let's take him to a hospital first.

186
00:06:58,320 --> 00:06:59,840
Jiusun, Jiusun, let's get out of here!

187
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,440
Come on, Jiusun.

188
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,320
No! Don't touch me!

189
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:03,360
What are you doing? I won't leave!

190
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:04,800
Jiusun, it's me!

191
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:05,600
What are you people doing?

192
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:06,240
It's me, Jiusun!

193
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:06,800
What are you doing?

194
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:09,520
You tell me now, why do you want me dead?

195
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:11,440
Why are you trying to kill me?

196
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:14,160
Why kill me?!

197
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:15,760
Why?!

198
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:17,600
Tell me why!

199
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:20,720
Why kill me?!

200
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:21,680
Tell me!

201
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:39,520
One pair of silver cups,

202
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,760
two pairs of silver chopsticks,

203
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,560
one felt table cloth,

204
00:12:43,228 --> 00:12:45,203
[Chen Duxiu, styled Zhongfu, Dean of Liberal Arts at Peking University]

205
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:48,080
four handkerchiefs,

206
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:49,280
Slow down, slow down.

207
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:51,280
Four handkerchiefs

208
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:52,480
Four handkerchiefs

209
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:57,200
to express our best wishes for Mr. Shizhi's wedding.

210
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:00,000
Shen Yimo,

211
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:02,080
Liu Wendian,

212
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:04,400
Chen Daqi,

213
00:13:03,774 --> 00:13:04,840
[Gao Yihan, Professor at Peking University]

214
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:06,480
Ma Xulun,

215
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:10,240
Cai Yuanpei,

216
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:10,960
Slow down.

217
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:12,080
Cai Yuanpei,

218
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:13,600
Zhang Shizhao,

219
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:15,280
Gao Yihan,

220
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:18,400
Liu Bannong,

221
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,280
Li Dazhao,

222
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:22,960
and you, Chen Duxiu.

223
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:29,040
Great! Now Shizhi is back to his hometown for his wedding.

224
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,480
As for this list of wedding gifts,

225
00:13:30,800 --> 00:13:31,920
you guys should make several copies of it

226
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,680
and post them in our offices,

227
00:13:32,084 --> 00:13:33,741
[Liu Bannong, Professor at Peking University]

228
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:34,880
and by the university entrance.

229
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,880
It's essentially a notice of appeasement.

230
00:13:37,280 --> 00:13:40,400
On one hand, it's a notice to the slanderers

231
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:42,080
asking them to cut the gossips.

232
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,000
On the other hand,

233
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:47,440
it's for the female poetry club members who are hankering after him,

234
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,280
so that they stop fantasizing.

235
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:50,960
Very well done, Zhongfu!

236
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:52,480
I can finally have a moment of peace!

237
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:55,520
No need to post the notice outside the dormitory of Shizhi and Yihan.

238
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:56,320
How so?

239
00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:56,960
Why though?

240
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:59,200
We should save some opportunities for the female poetry club members.

241
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,560
Even though Shizhi is now married,

242
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:02,240
Yihan can take over and receive their visits.

243
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:05,440
I have nothing like Shizhi's charisma.

244
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:06,480
No can do!

245
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:10,400
Give me the small piece, brother.

246
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:11,200
You eat the big piece.

247
00:14:11,680 --> 00:14:12,160
No.

248
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:13,520
I'll eat the small piece.

249
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:14,480
You eat the big piece.

250
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:15,280
Give it to me.

251
00:14:15,360 --> 00:14:16,240
No need.

252
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:18,320
You see?

253
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:18,880
Stop running away!

254
00:14:19,039 --> 00:14:20,375
[Zhao Renlan, Wife of Li Dazhao]

255
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,320
This is how it's done.

256
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,360
These are the secrets

257
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:25,680
I've been taught from the masters of masonry.

258
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:28,080
What are you doing?

259
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:30,560
Don't you start helping. Aren't you tired after a day of traveling?

260
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:31,920
Get a drink of water.

261
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:33,440
Take a break. We'll be done soon.

262
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:34,240
Say,

263
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,320
now that the house in Beijing has a kang-bed,

264
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:38,640
it's just like our house back home.

265
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:39,600
Auntie,

266
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:41,120
Beijing isn't like back home.

267
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,040
The winters in Beijing are so cold,

268
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:44,560
just a stove isn't enough.

269
00:14:44,640 --> 00:14:46,000
You need a kang-bed to be comfortable.

270
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:48,400
Well, this whole thing is so that the three of you

271
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:50,080
can sleep more comfortably.

272
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:50,880
That's right.

273
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:55,040
Don't you get your hands dirty.

274
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:57,520
You think I can be idle while you're working?

275
00:14:57,680 --> 00:14:58,880
Get down. Let me do it.

276
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,800
For my first time, I'm doing pretty well.

277
00:15:00,880 --> 00:15:01,600
Just ask Xiaoshan.

278
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:02,560
Right, Xiaoshan?

279
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:03,360
Sir,

280
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:04,560
you are very learned.

281
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,760
But in terms of doing work,

282
00:15:05,920 --> 00:15:07,360
you're not as good as us workers from Changxindian.

283
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:08,560
Did you hear that?

284
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:11,040
Alright, get down.

285
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:13,760
You still don't believe me.

286
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:15,600
Give me the knife.

287
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:17,920
You don't know how to do it either.

288
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:19,280
Oh, don't I?

289
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:21,840
Look.

290
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:27,440
Sir, it seems like Auntie really is more efficient than you are.

291
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:28,960
Why don't you let Auntie and I build the kang.

292
00:15:29,040 --> 00:15:29,600
If it's you and me,

293
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:31,200
auntie probably won't even get to sleep on the kang tonight.

294
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:33,520
Alright, stop getting in the way over there

295
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:34,400
and come down.

296
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:37,440
You even know how to do this work.

297
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:40,080
Careful coming up.

298
00:15:40,160 --> 00:15:40,560
Alrighty.

299
00:15:40,800 --> 00:15:42,160
Xiaoshan, lend me a hand.

300
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:46,000
Watch your hand.

301
00:15:46,080 --> 00:15:46,320
Alright.

302
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:48,160
I've laid bricks back home.

303
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,000
Watch your hand.

304
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,680
Lumpy, pass me a brick.

305
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:53,840
Auntie, who's Lumpy?

306
00:15:58,880 --> 00:15:59,680
Sir?

307
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,440
Your nickname is Lumpy?

308
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:06,880
Renlan,

309
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:13,600
I'm all grown up and you're still calling me by my nickname.

310
00:16:13,680 --> 00:16:15,520
How about Shouchang?

311
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:16,640
Why don't you call me by that?

312
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,480
But Xiaoshan isn't a stranger.

313
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,040
Fine, fine, fine.

314
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:22,320
In the future, when we're out

315
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:23,760
I'll call you Shouchang.

316
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:24,640
Shouchang.

317
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:26,800
But at home I'll still call you Lumpy.

318
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:28,880
Call me whatever you like.

319
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:29,840
Aye.

320
00:16:30,480 --> 00:16:32,640
Brother, you give me the small piece. YOu eat the big one.

321
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:34,480
No, thanks. I'll eat the small piece. You eat the big one.

322
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:36,880
Lumpy! Shouchang. Mr. Shouchang.

323
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:38,720
You'd better go look after your children.

324
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:39,760
Brother!

325
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,040
What's the matter?

326
00:16:41,760 --> 00:16:42,720
Give it to me.

327
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,640
Baohua and Xinghua, stop playing for a moment.

328
00:16:44,880 --> 00:16:45,280
Go inside.

329
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:47,440
Your Auntie Junman made you some new clothes.

330
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:48,480
Put it on.

331
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:49,600
And then

332
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:51,840
we can go eat instant-boiled mutton.

333
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:52,880
Mutton!

334
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:54,000
Hurry.

335
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,480
We're going to eat mutton!

336
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:59,680
What, mutton? I'll make some noodles for lunch.

337
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:02,160
Dumplings before leaving, noodles after arriving.

338
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:03,280
This is a good saying.

339
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:05,680
But today, for us?

340
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:06,960
No way.

341
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:10,480
It's good to eat some meat.

342
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,800
They're growing kids.

343
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:14,320
How can noodles compare to meat?

344
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:15,840
Xinghua, Boahua,

345
00:17:16,080 --> 00:17:18,320
Do you want to eat meat?

346
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,000
Or do you want to eat noodles?

347
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,040
Meat!

348
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:22,800
Hear that?

349
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:24,400
Spending money like water.

350
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,640
Auntie,

351
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:27,680
once your section is done,

352
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:29,120
the kang-bed will be pretty much finished.

353
00:17:30,080 --> 00:17:31,280
You've worked hard.

354
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:32,240
It's nothing, Auntie.

355
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:33,440
Once the clay in the kang has been heated,

356
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:34,400
you just need another layer.

357
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:35,360
You'll be able to use it after it dries.

358
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:36,160
Great.

359
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:39,040
Mr. Shouchang, we finished building the kang.

360
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:40,640
If there isn't anything else, I'll be getting back.

361
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:41,760
Why?

362
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:43,200
Didn't we agree?

363
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:44,400
To welcome your Auntie

364
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:45,840
we are all going to have mutton.

365
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:46,800
That's right.

366
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:48,560
I won't interrupt your family reunion.

367
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:50,400
My father's still at home. I can't leave him.

368
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:52,880
I forgot.

369
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:54,560
Give me a minute.

370
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:56,720
Eat before you leave.

371
00:17:56,880 --> 00:17:58,320
No, Auntie. I've still got things to take care of at home.

372
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:03,920
His father is sick. He needs to get back.

373
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,120
Here, Xiaoshan.

374
00:18:05,520 --> 00:18:06,400
I can't accept this, sir.

375
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:07,360
Take it, take it.

376
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:08,640
Auntie, I can't accept this money.

377
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:09,840
Why not?

378
00:18:10,080 --> 00:18:11,040
It's just a small token of my appreciation.

379
00:18:11,360 --> 00:18:11,760
Take it.

380
00:18:13,040 --> 00:18:13,680
Go.

381
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:14,880
Go.

382
00:18:17,920 --> 00:18:19,760
Thank you, sir. Thank you, auntie.

383
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:26,960
Go.

384
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:34,080
Go wash your hands.

385
00:18:38,480 --> 00:18:40,720
Father, we've changed. Let's go eat instant-pot mutton.

386
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:41,600
Good.

387
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:43,840
You've changed your clothes but your little faces are still grubby.

388
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:44,720
Come here.

389
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:46,880
Wash your faces and hands.

390
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,320
Nice and clean when we go out to eat.

391
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:49,920
Nice and clean.

392
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:51,960
I'll go get changed.

393
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:53,360
We'll leave once I change.

394
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:54,400
Mr. Shouchang.

395
00:18:55,520 --> 00:18:56,080
Please come in.

396
00:18:57,120 --> 00:18:57,680
Mr. Shouchang.

397
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:58,720
Come in, come in.

398
00:18:59,120 --> 00:18:59,840
Here, come in.

399
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:00,720
Sir.

400
00:19:00,960 --> 00:19:02,640
How did you know I moved here?

401
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:03,360
Hello, sir.

402
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:04,880
Sir.

403
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:08,880
Sir, the dean's office told us.

404
00:19:09,120 --> 00:19:10,480
You've just moved in.

405
00:19:10,720 --> 00:19:12,880
And here we are, suddenly visiting.

406
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:14,080
Excuse us.

407
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:14,480
It's true.

408
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:15,040
We've disturbed you.

409
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:16,080
What disturbance?

410
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:17,680
You're welcomed to come often.

411
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:20,480
Just so happens my wife is here.

412
00:19:20,560 --> 00:19:22,560
Wife, this is Zhong Xie and Hai Wei.

413
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:23,760
Two students of mine.

414
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:25,280
Hello mistress. Hello mistress.

415
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:26,240
Hello.

416
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,200
Hello.

417
00:19:27,440 --> 00:19:28,400
Hello.

418
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:30,880
Didn't know that the mistress just got here.

419
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:33,040
We apologize for our sudden visit.

420
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:33,760
Not at all, not at all.

421
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:35,600
Sit down and chat. No problem.

422
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:37,520
Here, come this way.

423
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:39,840
What's happened?

424
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:44,560
We didn't know the mistress would come today.

425
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:45,760
Very rude of us.

426
00:19:46,080 --> 00:19:48,320
Actually it's not a big deal.

427
00:19:49,120 --> 00:19:51,360
Let's go. We'll call on you another day.

428
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:52,240
Come back, come back.

429
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:54,960
Speak your mind. There must be a reason you came to visit.

430
00:19:55,120 --> 00:19:55,920
What's going on?

431
00:19:56,080 --> 00:19:57,440
Then I'll get to the point.

432
00:19:58,080 --> 00:19:59,680
It's like this.

433
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,720
Hai Wei has some problems with his tuition this semester.

434
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:05,440
He hasn't received the money sent from back home.

435
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:07,760
So the dean's office has asked him to write an IOU.

436
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,760
But he needs a teacher to be a guarantor.

437
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:11,760
So I said, why don't you find Mr. Shouchang.

438
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:13,040
But Hai Wei is thin skinned.

439
00:20:13,120 --> 00:20:13,920
He's embarrassed.

440
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:16,320
That's why I brought him along.

441
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:18,480
Hai wei,

442
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:19,840
this is nothing.

443
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,600
Do you really need to be embarrassed?

444
00:20:22,320 --> 00:20:23,600
It's just being a guarantor.

445
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:24,960
I'll do it.

446
00:20:26,160 --> 00:20:27,280
How much do you owe?

447
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:29,520
A deposit for five silver dollars.

448
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:32,480
Why bother being a guarantor?

449
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:33,040
I'll give it to you.

450
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:34,880
No need, sir.

451
00:20:35,840 --> 00:20:36,320
I'll give it to you.

452
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:36,960
Uh.

453
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:38,800
Uh, this won't do.

454
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:39,200
Uh.

455
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:40,000
Yes.

456
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:49,520
The travel expenses you gave me last time.

457
00:20:49,760 --> 00:20:50,800
There's three silver dollars left.

458
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:52,240
Give it to them.

459
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,040
Let's go, let's go.

460
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:56,640
Sir, we're going to get going.

461
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:57,520
Come back, come back.

462
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:01,440
Come.

463
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:04,560
Don't go running off.

464
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:07,360
Go pay.

465
00:21:07,520 --> 00:21:07,840
Sir.

466
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:09,760
I can't accept

467
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:11,440
this oney.

468
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,280
Why don't you just be my guarantor.

469
00:21:13,760 --> 00:21:14,560
That would be

470
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:15,680
the greatest help.

471
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:19,680
Give me your hand.

472
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:20,640
Sir.

473
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:23,360
Don't dawdle.

474
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,280
Quickly go to the dean's office and pay.

475
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:26,160
The next semester

476
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:27,360
is about to start.

477
00:21:28,560 --> 00:21:28,960
Zhang Xie,

478
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:29,920
go with him to pay.

479
00:21:30,160 --> 00:21:30,400
Go.

480
00:21:31,120 --> 00:21:31,360
Go.

481
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:33,440
The gentleman said so.

482
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:34,720
Just accept it.

483
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:38,880
Thank you, sir. Thank you Mr. Shouchang.

484
00:21:43,600 --> 00:21:44,320
Thank you mistress.

485
00:21:44,960 --> 00:21:45,680
Take care.

486
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:47,600
We'll be on our way.

487
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:02,160
Father, we're ready.

488
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:03,600
Let's go eat mutton.

489
00:22:03,920 --> 00:22:04,240
Instant-boiled mutton.

490
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:05,760
Instant-boiled mutton.

491
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:09,600
Baohua, Xinghua,

492
00:22:10,160 --> 00:22:10,560
come.

493
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:14,800
Father needs to explain something.

494
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:19,440
The disadvantages of eating meat.

495
00:22:23,040 --> 00:22:24,480
The most important disadvantage.

496
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:26,640
It gets stuck in your teeth.

497
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:29,120
And once it gets stuck in your teeth,

498
00:22:29,280 --> 00:22:30,000
we'd have to dig it out.

499
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:30,480
And digging?

500
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:32,240
It hurts so much.

501
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:32,960
No, I uh

502
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:33,840
can't eat it, can't eat it.

503
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:34,880
I won't get food stuck in my teeth.

504
00:22:35,120 --> 00:22:35,760
I have great teeth.

505
00:22:35,920 --> 00:22:36,800
I want to eat meat.

506
00:22:38,560 --> 00:22:40,720
You'll be uncomfortble when we dig it out.

507
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:41,600
I just want to eat meat.

508
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:43,760
Back home we always eat the noodles mother make.

509
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,040
I'm sick of it.

510
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,160
I want to eat meat.

511
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,200
Baohua, Xinghua,

512
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:48,720
what are you making a fuss for?

513
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:50,240
Going on about eating meat.

514
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,280
We'll stay home and eat the noodles I make.

515
00:22:52,560 --> 00:22:53,760
Mama's angry.

516
00:22:54,080 --> 00:22:54,880
No meat.

517
00:22:55,120 --> 00:22:55,760
It's good to eat noodles.

518
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:57,200
You won't get noodles stuck in your teeth.

519
00:22:57,360 --> 00:22:58,880
But I promise

520
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:00,880
I will take you two to eat instant-boiled mutton.

521
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:01,680
Two times.

522
00:23:01,920 --> 00:23:02,960
Is Mr. Shouchang home?

523
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:04,400
I'm here.

524
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:05,920
Hello.

525
00:23:06,400 --> 00:23:07,200
Hello, madame.

526
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:08,720
Mr. Zhao, why have you come?

527
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:11,760
Mr. Shouchang,

528
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:12,720
Today I'm not here

529
00:23:12,880 --> 00:23:13,440
to see you.

530
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:14,720
I'm here to see the madame.

531
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:15,920
To see me?

532
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:21,840
Madame,

533
00:23:22,080 --> 00:23:23,840
I'm here on the orders of Principal Cai Yuanpei

534
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:25,360
to give you you salary.

535
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:28,400
What does Mr. Cai mean by this?

536
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:29,920
Madame Li,

537
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:31,040
Mr. Cai knows

538
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:32,880
Director Li spends money like water,

539
00:23:33,040 --> 00:23:34,720
and takes pleasure in generously helping others.

540
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:35,760
He spends his salary

541
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:36,720
on charitable deeds.

542
00:23:36,960 --> 00:23:37,520
Therefore,

543
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:38,400
he decided

544
00:23:38,720 --> 00:23:40,400
to deduct thirty silver dollars

545
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:41,360
from Mr. Shouchang's salary every month.

546
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:43,120
And told me to personally give it to madame

547
00:23:43,200 --> 00:23:44,080
for household expenses.

548
00:23:44,480 --> 00:23:45,520
He knew you would arrive today

549
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:47,600
and that Mr. Shouchang won't have any money to help you settle down.

550
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:48,480
So

551
00:23:48,640 --> 00:23:49,840
he got me to quickly deliver the money.

552
00:23:50,080 --> 00:23:51,040
You should accept it.

553
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:54,560
Shouchang,

554
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:56,640
is this appropriate?

555
00:23:57,280 --> 00:23:57,920
It is.

556
00:23:58,480 --> 00:23:59,200
Take it.

557
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:00,640
Here.

558
00:24:01,760 --> 00:24:02,400
Thank you.

559
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:07,520
Mr. Cai has really found a solution to my emergency.

560
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:09,040
Mr. Zhao,

561
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:11,280
please pass on my thanks

562
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:12,000
to Mr. Cai.

